This paper presents a model for unsupervised topic discovery in text corpora using neural network models and probabilistic latent semantic analysis (PLSA) assumptions. This work involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
